
1. Download the mongodb from the following website

	https://www.filehorse.com/download-mongodb/33269/download/

2. Then install the mongodb in your system by double click on .msi file
3. Once after successfull installation, create new folder in D or E drive for data
4. open the command prompt and type following cmd
	 "C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\3.6\bin\mongod.exe" --dbpath d:\test\mongodb\data

5. Then go to mongoDB foler where you install the mongo db like
	"C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\3.6\bin\
6. Then double click on mongo option, then it will open the mongo db command prompt there we can create,insert operation for mongo db

7. to create db in mongo use dbname
8. Then we can write code in node js to create collection or to insert delete, update values
	